<i>noun</i>: 힐책 [힐책], 힐문 [힐문], 핀잔 [핀잔], 책망 [챙망], 질타 [질타], 질책 [질책], 지청구 [지청구], 욕 [욕], 야단 [야ː단], 비판 [비ː판], 면박 [면ː박], 견책 [견ː책], 가책 [가ː책] <i>verb</i>: 힐책하다 [힐채카다], 힐문하다 [힐문하다], 혼내다 [혼내다], 허물하다 [허물하다], 핀잔하다 [핀잔하다], 핀잔주다 [핀잔주다], 책하다 [채카다], 책망하다 [챙망하다], 질타하다 [질타하다], 질책하다 [질채카다 ], 면박하다 [면ː바카다], 닦아세우다 [다까세우다], 나무라다 [나무라다], 꾸짖다 [꾸짇따], 꾸지람하다 [꾸지람하다], 꾸중하다 [꾸중하다], 견책하다 [견ː채카다], 가책하다 [가ː채카다] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>힐책 [힐책]</dt><br>
<dd>rebuke; reprimand; blame</dd><br>
<dd>잘못된 점을 꾸짖어 알아듣게 말함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of scolding someone for his/her fault in a way that he/she will understand well.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>힐문 [힐문]</dt><br>
<dd>reprimand; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>흠이나 잘못을 잡아 따져 물음.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of holding somebody responsible for a mistake or flaw and scolding him/her for that.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>핀잔 [핀잔]</dt><br>
<dd>telling-off; scolding; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>못마땅하게 여겨 꾸짖는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of scolding someone due to one's discontent with him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>책망 [챙망]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖거나 나무람.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of scolding or blaming a person for his/her fault.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>질타 [질타]</dt><br>
<dd>rebuke; reproof</dd><br>
<dd>큰 소리로 잘못을 나무람.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of loudly scolding someone about his/her mistake or wrongdoing.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>질책 [질책]</dt><br>
<dd>reprimand; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 엄하게 나무람.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of an elder scolding a younger person severely for a mistake or wrongdoing.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>지청구 [지청구]</dt><br>
<dd>1. reprimand; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 꾸짖는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Words spoken by an elder to point out a mistake or wrongdoing of a younger person.</dd><br>
<dd>2. blame</dd><br>
<dd>이유 없이 남을 탓하고 원망하는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Words spoken to resentfully accuse another person, without any special reason.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>욕 [욕]</dt><br>
<dd>1. foul language; abusive language</dd><br>
<dd>남을 무시하거나 비난하는 상스러운 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Vulgar words used to ignore or criticize someone.</dd><br>
<dd>2. reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 해서 듣는 꾸지람.</dd><br>
<dd>A scolding that one gets when one makes a mistake.</dd><br>
<dd>3. shame; humiliation</dd><br>
<dd>부끄럽고 치욕스러운 일.</dd><br>
<dd>Something disgraceful and dishonorable.</dd><br>
<dd>4. labor; pains</dd><br>
<dd>(속된 말로) 수고.</dd><br>
<dd>(slang) Trouble.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>야단 [야ː단]</dt><br>
<dd>1. uproar; tumult; clamor</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일 때문에 시끄럽게 자꾸 떠들거나 소란을 일으킴.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making a noise or making a row due to something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. scolding; chiding; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람의 잘못을 큰소리로 혼냄.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of criticizing someone's mistake in a loud voice.</dd><br>
<dd>3. trouble; predicament; quandary</dd><br>
<dd>매우 곤란한 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A very awkward situation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>비판 [비ː판]</dt><br>
<dd>criticism; critical judgment; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>무엇에 대해 자세히 따져 옳고 그름을 밝히거나 잘못된 점을 지적함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of examining something closely and making a judgment between right and wrong, or pointing out what is wrong.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>면박 [면ː박]</dt><br>
<dd>rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴을 마주 하여 꾸짖거나 창피를 줌.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of scolding or humiliating a person face to face.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>견책 [견ː책]</dt><br>
<dd>reprimand; censure; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖고 알아듣도록 말함.</dd><br>
<dd>Scolding and correcting someone's mistake or fault.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>가책 [가ː책]</dt><br>
<dd>admonishment; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>자기나 남의 잘못을 꾸짖음.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of scolding oneself or others for doing something wrong.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>힐책하다 [힐채카다]</dt><br>
<dd>rebuke; reprimand; blame</dd><br>
<dd>잘못된 점을 꾸짖어 알아듣게 말하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold someone for his/her fault in a way that he/she will understand well.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>힐문하다 [힐문하다]</dt><br>
<dd>reprimand; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>흠이나 잘못을 잡아 따져 묻다.</dd><br>
<dd>To hold somebody responsible for a mistake or flaw and scold him/her for that.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>혼내다 [혼내다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; rebuke; punish</dd><br>
<dd>심하게 꾸지람을 하거나 벌을 주다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold someone harshly or punish him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>허물하다 [허물하다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; criticize; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못 저지른 실수를 꾸짖다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold someone for making a mistake.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>핀잔하다 [핀잔하다]</dt><br>
<dd>tell off; scold; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>못마땅하게 여겨 꾸짖다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold someone due to one's discontent with him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>핀잔주다 [핀잔주다]</dt><br>
<dd>tell off; scold; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>못마땅하게 여겨 꾸짖다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold someone due to one's discontent with him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>책하다 [채카다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖거나 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold or blame a person for his/her fault.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>책망하다 [챙망하다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; reproach; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖거나 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold or blame a person for his/her fault.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>질타하다 [질타하다]</dt><br>
<dd>rebuke; reprimand; reprove</dd><br>
<dd>큰 소리로 잘못을 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold someone about his/her mistake or wrongdoing loudly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>질책하다 [질채카다 ]</dt><br>
<dd>reprimand; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 엄하게 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an elder to scold a younger person severely for a mistake or wrongdoing.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>면박하다 [면ː바카다]</dt><br>
<dd>rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴을 마주하여 꾸짖거나 창피를 주다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold or humiliate a person face to face.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>닦아세우다 [다까세우다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>꼼짝 못하게 몰아붙여서 심하게 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>To corner someone and scold him/her harshly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>나무라다 [나무라다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. scold; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖어 잘 알아듣게 말하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold someone for his/her fault in a way that he/she will understand well.</dd><br>
<dd>2. criticize</dd><br>
<dd>사람의 말이나 행동, 성격에서 잘못된 점이나 부족한 점을 지적하여 말하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To point out and let one know of one's mistake or the weakness of one's words, actions, or personality.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>꾸짖다 [꾸짇따]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 몹시 나무라다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an elder to severely point out a mistake or wrongdoing of a younger person.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>꾸지람하다 [꾸지람하다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 꾸짖다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an elder to point out a mistake or wrongdoing of a younger person.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>꾸중하다 [꾸중하다]</dt><br>
<dd>scold; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 꾸짖다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an elder to point out a mistake or wrongdoing of a younger person.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>견책하다 [견ː채카다]</dt><br>
<dd>reprimand; censure; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖고 알아듣도록 말하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold and correct someone's mistake or fault.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>가책하다 [가ː채카다]</dt><br>
<dd>admonish; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>자기나 남의 잘못을 꾸짖다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scold oneself or another person for doing something wrong.</dd><br>
</li>
